 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ch03-title",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["# Chapter 3: Scalable Multi-Agent Architectures\n", "\n", "As agent systems grow, they form **topologies**—structural patterns for how\n", "agents connect and route work. Topology choice has direct implications for\n", "fault tolerance, latency, and correctness.\n", "\n", "**Concepts covered:**\n", "- Star topology (hub-and-spoke orchestration)\n", "- Mesh topology (peer-to-peer)\n", "- Ring topology (pipeline/sequential)\n", "- Tree topology (hierarchical decomposition)\n", "- Trade-off analysis"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "ch03-setup",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": ["import sys, os, asyncio\n", "sys.path.insert(0, os.path.abspath('../..'))\n", "\n", "from core.topologies.multi_agent import (\n", "    AgentNode, MeshTopology, RingTopology, StarTopology, TreeTopology,\n", ")\n", "print('Multi-agent topology module ready.')"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ch03-star-intro",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## 3.1 Star Topology: Hub-and-Spoke\n", "\n", "A central **orchestrator agent** receives all tasks and fans work out to specialist leaf agents.\n", "Simple to reason about—but the hub is a single point of failure and a potential bottleneck.\n", "\n", "```\n", "           [Leaf A: Research]\n", "                 |\n", "[All input] → [Hub] → [Leaf B: Write]\n", "                 |\n", "           [Leaf C: Review]\n", "```"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "ch03-star-demo",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": ["import asyncio\n", "\n", "async def hub_process(task):\n", "    return f'[Hub decomposed]: {task}'\n", "\n", "async def research_agent(task):\n", "    return f'[Research]: Gathered info for \'{task}\''\n", "\n", "async def writer_agent(task):\n", "    return f'[Writer]: Draft created from \'{task}\''\n", "\n", "async def review_agent(task):\n", "    return f'[Review]: Approved \'{task}\''\n", "\n", "async def demo_star():\n", "    star = StarTopology(hub_id='hub')\n", "    star.add_node(AgentNode('hub', 'Orchestrator', hub_process))\n", "    star.add_node(AgentNode('research', 'ResearchAgent', research_agent))\n", "    star.add_node(AgentNode('writer', 'WriterAgent', writer_agent))\n", "    star.add_node(AgentNode('review', 'ReviewAgent', review_agent))\n", "\n", "    results = await star.route('Generate article about microservices', sender_id='user')\n", "    print(f'Star topology results ({len(results)} leaf responses):')\n", "    for r in results:\n", "        print(f'  {r}')\n", "\n", "asyncio.run(demo_star())"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ch03-mesh-intro",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## 3.2 Mesh Topology: Peer-to-Peer\n", "\n", "Any agent can message any other via explicit **edges**.\n", "Maximum flexibility and fault tolerance (no single hub), but O(n²) complexity.\n", "Best for: real-time coordination, consensus protocols, swarm intelligence."]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "ch03-mesh-demo",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": ["import asyncio\n", "\n", "async def validator(msg): return f'[Validate]: {msg}'\n", "async def enricher(msg): return f'[Enrich]: {msg}'\n", "async def notifier(msg): return f'[Notify]: {msg}'\n", "\n", "async def demo_mesh():\n", "    mesh = MeshTopology()\n", "    mesh.add_node(AgentNode('ingest', 'Ingestor', lambda m: asyncio.coroutine(lambda: m)()))\n", "    mesh.add_node(AgentNode('validate', 'Validator', validator))\n", "    mesh.add_node(AgentNode('enrich', 'Enricher', enricher))\n", "    mesh.add_node(AgentNode('notify', 'Notifier', notifier))\n", "\n", "    # Define explicit routing edges\n", "    mesh.add_edge('ingest', 'validate')\n", "    mesh.add_edge('ingest', 'enrich')\n", "    mesh.add_edge('validate', 'notify')\n", "\n", "    results = await mesh.route('order:ORD-555', sender_id='ingest')\n", "    print(f'Mesh results from ingest node:')\n", "    for r in results:\n", "        print(f'  {r}')\n", "\n", "asyncio.run(demo_mesh())"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ch03-ring-intro",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## 3.3 Ring Topology: Sequential Pipeline\n", "\n", "Work flows through agents in a **fixed order** — each stage transforms the artifact.\n", "Natural fit for ETL, document processing, or multi-stage validation.\n", "\n", "Critical limitation: one broken stage halts the entire pipeline."]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "ch03-ring-demo",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": ["import asyncio\n", "\n", "async def extract(data): return {'raw': data, 'extracted': True}\n", "async def transform(data): data['transformed'] = True; return data\n", "async def validate(data): data['valid'] = len(data.get('raw', '')) > 0; return data\n", "async def load(data): return f'Loaded: {data}'\n", "\n", "async def demo_ring():\n", "    ring = RingTopology()\n", "    ring.add_node(AgentNode('extract', 'Extractor', extract))\n", "    ring.add_node(AgentNode('transform', 'Transformer', transform))\n", "    ring.add_node(AgentNode('validate', 'Validator', validate))\n", "    ring.add_node(AgentNode('load', 'Loader', load))\n", "    ring.set_order(['extract', 'transform', 'validate', 'load'])\n", "\n", "    trace = await ring.route('customer_event_2024.json', sender_id='source')\n", "    print('Ring pipeline trace (each stage output):')\n", "    for i, step in enumerate(trace, 1):\n", "        print(f'  Stage {i}: {step}')\n", "\n", "asyncio.run(demo_ring())"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ch03-tree-intro",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## 3.4 Tree Topology: Hierarchical Decomposition\n", "\n", "The root agent breaks a complex task and **delegates sub-tasks** to subtrees.\n", "Each subtree can itself contain further decompositions.\n", "\n", "This is the natural shape of Manager → Team Lead → Individual Contributor agent hierarchies."]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "ch03-tree-demo",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": ["import asyncio\n", "\n", "async def planner(task): return f'[Plan]: {task}'\n", "async def backend_lead(task): return f'[Backend Lead]: {task}'\n", "async def frontend_lead(task): return f'[Frontend Lead]: {task}'\n", "async def api_dev(task): return f'[API Dev]: {task}'\n", "async def db_dev(task): return f'[DB Dev]: {task}'\n", "async def ui_dev(task): return f'[UI Dev]: {task}'\n", "\n", "async def demo_tree():\n", "    tree = TreeTopology(root_id='planner')\n", "    for nid, name, fn in [\n", "        ('planner', 'Planner', planner),\n", "        ('backend_lead', 'BackendLead', backend_lead),\n", "        ('frontend_lead', 'FrontendLead', frontend_lead),\n", "        ('api_dev', 'APIDev', api_dev),\n", "        ('db_dev', 'DBDev', db_dev),\n", "        ('ui_dev', 'UIDev', ui_dev),\n", "    ]:\n", "        tree.add_node(AgentNode(nid, name, fn))\n", "    tree.add_children('planner', ['backend_lead', 'frontend_lead'])\n", "    tree.add_children('backend_lead', ['api_dev', 'db_dev'])\n", "    tree.add_children('frontend_lead', ['ui_dev'])\n", "\n", "    leaves = await tree.route('Build order management feature', sender_id='pm')\n", "    print('Tree dispatch results (leaf agents):')\n", "    for r in leaves:\n", "        print(f'  {r}')\n", "\n", "asyncio.run(demo_tree())"]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ch03-tradeoffs",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": ["## 3.5 Topology Trade-offs\n", "\n", "| Topology | Fault Tolerance | Max Scalability | Complexity | Best For |\n", "|----------|----------------|-----------------|------------|----------|\n", "| **Star** | Low (hub SPOF) | Medium | Low | Simple orchestration |\n", "| **Mesh** | High (no SPOF) | Low (O(n²)) | High | Real-time collaboration |\n", "| **Ring** | Low (one stage) | High | Low | Pipelines, ETL |\n", "| **Tree** | Medium | High | Medium | Hierarchical tasks |\n", "\n", "On **Azure Container Apps**: each topology maps to a set of Container Apps\n", "communicating via Dapr pub/sub (Service Bus) or Dapr service invocation."]
  }
 ],
